ASA Website Installation Report
Installation Guide
This guide will take you through the steps to install and set up the ASA Website on your local machine.

Prerequisites
Node.js installed on your computer. 
MongoDB installed on your computer or access to a MongoDB database. 
A code editor (like Visual Studio Code) installed. 

Step-by-Step Installation
Clone the Repository on the github link

Open your terminal and run:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/username/repolink

cd ASA-website
Install Dependencies: Install the Node.js dependencies defined in the package.json file.

Install Dependencies

In the terminal, run:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Environment Setup: Create a .env file in the root directory of the project. Add the necessary environment variables like MONGODB_URI.

Environment Setup

Example of .env content:

bash
Copy code
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/asaDatabase
Run the Application: Start the server using Node.js.

Run Application

In the terminal, run:

bash
Copy code
node server.js
Access the Website: Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:3000 (or the port you set in your environment).

Access Website

You should now see the ASA Website running locally on your machine.

Typical Use Cases
Browsing Upcoming Events
Users can view a list of upcoming events on the ASA Website. Each event has details and an RSVP option.


Alumni Spotlight
The Alumni Spotlight section features notable alumni, showcasing their achievements and contributions.


Making Donations
Users can contribute to the ASA by clicking the 'Donate' button, which redirects them to a secure donation page.


Newsletter Subscription
Members and visitors can subscribe to the ASA newsletter for regular updates and news.


These use cases highlight the core functionalities of the ASA Website, emphasizing the features that are well-implemented and useful for the end-users.
